Vintage 1974 Jack-In-The-Box 5pc Set Bendable Buddies Fast Food Restaurant Premium Toy Figures
Aus GRACEFULPAST Hi! This is a cute 35 year old rubber figures set made and given by the Jack in the Box fast food restaurant back in 1974. Their names are as follows:
"Jack"(1qty)4"tall - The ringleader himself! Through the 70's, his big head graced the drive through lanes at most restaurants.
"ONION RING THING"(1qty)3.5"tall - A Hyper little fellow that always seemed to be goofing around and shouting Hoo Hoo!
"Small Fry"(1qty)3.25"tall) - Small Fry was a kid that was always hanging around asking Jack questions. The storybooks depicted him as being a little kid, but the bendy fig makes him look like an awkward teenager that's always half asleep.
"SECRET SAUCE AGENT"(2qty)3.5"tall - I'm not quite sure what Secret Sauce Agent contributed to Jack's Clique. Maybe his job was to guard the secret sauce from Ronald and the Burger King? He always had a big grin on his face, and was constantly peeking around corners and hiding.
Last but not least we have the"HAMBURGERMEISTER"(1qty)3.5"tall - This little guy hails from Germany and was always clad in lederhosen. He was known for cracking bad jokes and had a thick German accent.
You will receive 2 Secret Sauce Agent figures. All figures are in good condition with minor paint loss and needing a gentle cleaning. Small fry is in the roughest condition with chew marks on his hands and his nose has been snipped. They display great and are getting very hard to find especially in a set. Thanks for coming by!
